==English==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|yeerly}}, {{m|enm|yerely}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġēarlīċ}}, {{m|en|ġērlīċ||yearly, of the year, annual}}, equivalent to {{af|en|year|-ly}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|yerelie||yearly}}, {{cog|stq|jierelk||yearly}}, {{cog|fy|jierliks||yearly}}, {{cog|nl|jaarlijks||yearly}}, {{cog|af|jaarlijks||yearly}}, {{cog|de|jährlich||yearly}}, {{cog|da|årlig||yearly}}, {{cog|nb|årlig||yearly}}, {{cog|nn|årleg||yearly}}, {{cog|sv|årlig||yearly}}, {{cog|is|árlegur||yearly}}.
